<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-07-12T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-07-12T00:00:00-05:00" n="1431" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1431">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 312.52/369.</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Spanish Ambassador</gloss>
                                    to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Spanish Embassy</hi>, <lb/>
                                        <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-07-12">
                                        <hi rend="italic">July 12, 1914</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Mr Secretary</hi>: I have the honor to inform
                                your excellency that it appears from a telegram I have just received
                                from the Minister of Spain in Mexico that the Constitutionalists at
                                Zacatecas have shot three priests and expelled about twenty. Senor
                                Cologan adds that several Sisters of St. Therese are in hiding at
                                that place.</p>
                            <p>I beg your excellency kindly to take an interest in the fate of those
                                unfortunate people and commend to your attention more particularly
                                the Sisters of St. Therese of whom several are Spanish.</p>
                            <p>I avail [etc.]</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Juan Riaño</hi></signed>.</closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>